<p>
    Ecars has a network of over 1,200 public, standard and fast charge points across the country. 
    This includes over 300 public charge points in Northern Ireland. These are found in convenient on-street locations, 
    in car-parks, popular retail and leisure venues, as well as at key transport hubs nationwide. All charge points are 
    accessed via a single charge point access card. The charging time for standard charge points depends on the model of
    vehicle and how full the car battery is when it is plugged in. A full re-charge can take from one to eight hours using
    the standard charge point network.
</p>

